Integrate Git with Jenkins

Objective: Integrate Git with Jenkins

Tools required: Git and Jenkins


Steps to be followed:
1.	Install Git plugin


Step 1: Open the browser, and go to Jenkins dashboard by typing localhost:8080 in your browser
Step 2: Provide the credentials, and click on Sign in
Step 3: Click on Manage Jenkins. From the list of options, choose Manage Plugins
Step 4: Under the Available tab, select Git Plugin
Step 5: Click on Install without restart, and the plugin will be installed
